cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel network architecture that improves the feature fusion process in salient object detection, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on several benchmarks, which involves performance evaluation and comparison, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
